This is a change originally made for OpenVR which is needed to apply to core if we want to implement OpenVR as a GDNative module.

It simply exposes the OpenGL texture ID of a texture to the outside world. In OpenVR you need to send this texture ID for the render targets of the two eyes to OpenVR for further processing and output to the HMD (you don't have direct access to the HMDs screen and OpenVR handles lens distortion). 

@reduz , @Hinsbart
